$ HTML: DOCTYPE declaration

The DOCTYPE declaration of a HTML document determines in which → development/web/browser/layout-engine[layout mode] a browser renders a document. In order to render a document in *full standard mode*, the following DOCTYPE declaration needs to be
put at the start of a HTML document:
code {
<!DOCTYPE html>
code }

If there is *anything* before the `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration, the document will be assumed to be in quirks mode.

